# <%= current_page.data.title %>

## Context

MOJ Forms uses the Microsoft services:

- SSO – Single Sign-On for accessing MOJ Forms Editor
- Sending submission data to MS SharePoint Lists

These have Application Registrations (app reg) to enable this.

## Prerequisites

1. Access to the fb-editor-deploy repo
2. Added GPG key to the git-crypt in the fb-editor-deploy repo
3. Permissions to the app in MS Azure for both live and devl tenants
4. Access to the moj-forms Auth0 tenant

> Note: The TA for the team is the owner for the app registrations

## SSO - Authentication Connection

MOJ forms uses Auth0 to manage the SSO into MOJ Forms.

> Note: SSO into MOJ Forms did include via Google, this has migrated, the auth may not work or auth via MS.

There are 4 Enterprise Azure ADs, with domains they cover:

| AD             | Domain                                            |
| -------------- | ------------------------------------------------- |
| Azure-CICA     | cica.gov.uk                                       |
| CCRC-Azure     | ccrc.gov.uk                                       |
| HMCTSnet-Azure | hmcts.net                                         |
| moj-azure      | justice.gov.uk                                    |
|                | digital.justice.gov.uk - uses MOJ MS Entra ID now |
|                | ospt.gov.uk                                       |
|                | judicialappointments.gov.uk                       |
|                | judicialombudsman.gov.uk                          |
|                | ospt.gov.uk                                       |
|                | publicguardian.gov.uk                             |

We have access to only the moj-azure connection to create a new secret.

For CICA, CCRC and HMCTS.net you will need to raise a request or post a slack message
in #staff-identity-authentication-services channel for help to manage these.

## Rotating
__Azure__

1. Open [portal.azure.com](https://portal.azure.com/)
2. Find the SSO application in the portal
3. Secrets & tokens
4. Client secrets tab and New client secret
5. Name, add an expiry date then copy the secret (store in 1Password if using it later)

__Auth0__

1. moj-forms tenant
2. Authentication
3. Enterprise
4. Microsoft Azure AD
5. moj-azure
6. Edit client secret
7. Add new secret
8. save

[Auth0 Guidance](https://auth0.com/docs/authenticate/identity-providers/enterprise-identity-providers/azure-active-directory/v2)

> If the tokens between Auth0 and the Editor need changing,
these will be in the fb-eeditor-deply repo.

## Add New Domain

In some cases you may need to add a domain,
currently this involves adding the domain to the long list of buttons
on the Auth0 log in screen.

### Add to allow list
__Auth0__

1. moj-forms tenant
2. Actions
3. Library
4. Email_domain_allowlist
5. Add the new domain into the list
6. Save draft, deploy

__fb-editor__

Add into the [MOJ Form Editor Repo](https://github.com/ministryofjustice/fb-editor/blob/main/config/initializers/allowed_domains.rb)

### Update login screen

This is to add the domain into the long list of buttons to log in.

__Auth0__

1. moj-forms tenant
2. Branding
3. Universal Login
4. Advanced Login
5. Login
6. Customise Login Page
7. Update the javascript with the new connection and button.

> WARNING: This changes both test and live. Update with caution.

## MS SharePoint Lists

### Editor
Set up for the Test Editor and Environments

__Azure__

1. Open [portal.azure.com](https://portal.azure.com/)
2. Log in with the devl account (name@devl.justice.gov.uk)
3. moj-forms-development
4. Manage > certificates & secrets
5. Client secrets > + new client secret
6. Add name and expiry date
7. Copy Value - Add to 1Passwoird for safe keeping

Update the deploy repo

__fb-editor-deploy__

```bash
git pull
git checkout –b rotate-lists-secret-test-yymm
git-crypt unlock
echo thesecretfromabove | base64
```

Update `secrets/test-secrets-values.yaml` > ms_admin_app_secret

```bash
git add [the files]
git commit –m “Updated the list test secret”
git-crypt lock
git push
```
### Submitter
__fb-submitter-deploy__

```bash
git pull
git checkout –b rotate-lists-secret-test-yymm
gGit-crypt unlock
echo thesecretfromabove | base64
```

Add `secrets/test-dev-secrets-values.yaml` > ms_admin_app_secret

Add `secrets/test-production-secrets-values.yaml` > ms_admin_app_secret

```bash
git add [the files]
git commit –m “Updated the list test secret”
git-crypt lock
git push
```

__Live environment__

Exactly the same process but log in with justice account for portal.azure.com.

Use live-dev and live-production for the enviroment secrets.
